This results in the following output:

```
A=12
B=12
C=8
```

I didn't ask for thread switch in any of the calls.

Another issues is that ReadAsync ignores ReadTimeout / WriteTimeout. Just hangs forever if UART device never replies back.

In this code `C` fails to implement `I2.M2()`.  When I ask the IDE to "implement interface explicitly", it adds an implementation for `I2.M2()` and *also* an unnecessary implementation for `I2.M()` which is already implemented.  I only wanted the IDE to add an implementation for the method that was not already implemented.

``` csharp
interface I1
{
    void M();
}
interface I2 : I1
{
    void M();
    void M2();
}

class C : I2
{
    public void M() { }
    void I1.M() => M();
}
```

_This issue has been moved from [a ticket on Developer Community](https://developercommunity.visualstudio.com/content/idea/900532/c-intellisense-suggestion-hide-get-only-properties.html)._

---
When using an object initializer GET only properties aren't valid so they shouldn't be suggested by intellisense.

```
public class Example
{
    public Example()
    {
        var exampleInitializer = new ExampleInitializerClass
        {
            Property1 = "prop 1",
            Property2 = "prop 2",
            GetOnlyProperty // This can't be set and clutters the intellisense suggestions
        };
    }
}

public class ExampleInitializerClass
{
    public string GetOnlyProperty => "Example";

public string Property1 { get; set; }
    public string Property2 { get; set; }
}
```

